<paragraph blockId="28.[478,906,795,851]" box="[580,804,827,851]" pageId="28" pageNumber="909">
(
<figureCitation box="[589,709,827,851]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="22.[212,279,1433,1455]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,168,1400]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[213,1170,168,1401]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figure 11. Morphological characters of different species. (A––D) Galumna iranensis Mahunka et Akrami, 2001. (A) Lateral view of proterosoma (arrow indicates dorsosejugal porose area Ad); (B) dorsal view of prodorsum (arrow indicates central carina of rostrum); (C) lateral part of notogaster; (D) lateral view of sensillus. (E–H) Pergalumna microtuberculata sp. nov. (E) Posterior view of notogaster showing porose areas A3 and Ap; (F) porose area Aa; (G) posterior part of notogaster; (H) pteromorph." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4006697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4006697/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="909">Figures 11</figureCitation>
and 
