<subSubSection lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="912" pageId="30" pageNumber="911" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[212,1172,1595,1691]" box="[212,310,1595,1619]" pageId="30" pageNumber="911">
<heading box="[212,310,1595,1619]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="911" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,310,1595,1619]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="911">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[212,1172,1595,1691]" lastBlockId="31.[144,1104,168,862]" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="912" pageId="30" pageNumber="911">
<taxonomicName authority="Bayartogtokh &amp; Akrami, 2014" authorityName="Bayartogtokh &amp; Akrami" authorityYear="2014" box="[212,550,1635,1659]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="911" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microtuberculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[212,550,1635,1659]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="911">Pergalumna microtuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[568,666,1636,1659]" pageId="30" pageNumber="911" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is unique among the known species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grandjean" authorityYear="1936" box="[212,346,1667,1691]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="911" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[212,346,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="911">Pergalumna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of following features, namely: large, nearly elongate triangular porose area 
<emphasis box="[417,449,169,192]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">Aa</emphasis>
, the outer part of which is widened, but inner part is narrowed; very slightly dilated head of sensillus; presence of small central tooth of rostrum; dense granules and longitudinal striations on epimeral region; far anterior position of notogastral lyrifissure 
<emphasis box="[547,575,265,288]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">im</emphasis>
, and microtubercles on humeral region and posterior part of notogaster.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[144,1104,168,862]" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">
Among the known species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grandjean" authorityYear="1936" box="[525,659,328,352]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[525,659,328,352]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">Pergalumna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Oudemans, 1915)" baseAuthorityName="Oudemans" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[675,1099,328,352]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altera">
<emphasis box="[675,881,328,352]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">Pergalumna altera</emphasis>
(Oudemans, 1915)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Berlese, 1920)" baseAuthorityName="Berlese" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[144,621,359,383]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comparanda">
<emphasis box="[144,428,359,383]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">Pergalumna comparanda</emphasis>
(Berlese, 1920)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Berlese, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Berlese" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[642,1099,359,384]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formicaria">
<emphasis box="[642,907,359,384]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">Pergalumna formicaria</emphasis>
(Berlese, 1914)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Perez-Inigo, 1990" authorityName="Perez-Inigo" authorityYear="1990" box="[144,626,391,415]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minoricana">
<emphasis box="[144,413,391,415]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">Pergalumna minoricana</emphasis>
Pérez-Iñigo, 1990
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Berlese, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Berlese" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[693,1103,391,415]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nervosa">
<emphasis box="[693,922,391,415]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">Pergalumna nervosa</emphasis>
(Berlese, 1914)
</taxonomicName>
are similar to the new species in the structure of porose area 
<emphasis box="[902,934,424,447]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">Aa</emphasis>
and sensillus. However, two common species in the Palaearctic region, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Oudemans" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[819,919,455,479]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altera">
<emphasis box="[819,919,455,479]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">P. altera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Berlese" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[984,1103,456,479]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nervosa">
<emphasis box="[984,1103,456,479]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">P. nervosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are different from the new species in the slightly widened outer part of porose area 
<emphasis box="[144,176,519,542]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">Aa</emphasis>
; round porose area 
<emphasis box="[425,454,519,546]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">
A 
<subScript attach="left" box="[444,454,529,546]" fontSize="7" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
; reticulate structure of pteromorph; smoothly rounded rostrum, and far larger body size.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[144,1104,168,862]" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">
Two other species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Berlese" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[402,570,583,607]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comparanda">
<emphasis box="[402,570,583,607]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">P. comparanda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Berlese" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[627,774,583,607]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formicaria">
<emphasis box="[627,774,583,607]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">P. formicaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are distinguishable from the new species by the different size of interlamellar seta (seta 
<emphasis box="[880,900,615,638]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">in</emphasis>
is far longer in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Berlese" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[144,314,646,670]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comparanda">
<emphasis box="[144,314,646,670]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">P. comparanda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but much shorter in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Berlese" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[574,725,647,671]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formicaria">
<emphasis box="[574,725,647,671]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">P. formicaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); swollen head of sensillus; relatively posterior position of notogastral lyrifissure 
<emphasis box="[702,730,679,702]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">im</emphasis>
, and smoothly rounded rostrum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[144,1104,168,862]" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">
The Mediterranean species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perez-Inigo" authorityYear="1990" box="[518,678,711,734]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minoricana">
<emphasis box="[518,678,711,734]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">P. minoricana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the new species in the structure of porose area 
<emphasis box="[432,464,742,765]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">Aa</emphasis>
, conspicuously widened in both inner and outer parts; relatively longer interlamellar seta, extending well beyond tip of rostrum; relatively posterior position of notogastral lyrifissure 
<emphasis box="[632,660,807,830]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">im</emphasis>
; smoothly rounded rostrum, and much larger body size.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="912" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="31.[144,1104,928,1025]" box="[144,265,928,952]" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">
<heading box="[144,265,928,952]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[144,265,928,952]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[144,1104,928,1025]" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bayartogtokh &amp; Akrami" authorityYear="2014" box="[392,579,968,992]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microtuberculata">
<emphasis box="[392,579,968,992]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">microtuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the presence of small tubercles on humeral region and posterior part of notogaster.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="912" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="31.[144,1103,1090,1187]" box="[144,234,1090,1114]" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">
<heading box="[144,234,1090,1114]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[144,234,1090,1114]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">Ecology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[144,1103,1090,1187]" pageId="31" pageNumber="912">
This species is an inhabitant of the lowland pasture soil, and the specimens were found under graminoid grasses (
<taxonomicName box="[512,609,1162,1186]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="31" pageNumber="912" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
